All Classes and Interfaces

Class
Description
AbsGameBoard
 
BoardPosition
This class is used to keep track of an individual cell on the board
GameBoard
This class will contain our game board for the fast implementation
GameBoardMem
This class will contain our game board for the memory implementation
GameSetupController
The GameSetupController class will handle communication between our GameSetupScreen and start a new game when all the required fields to build an IGameBoard is met.
GameSetupScreen
This class contains the code to create and layout the GUI for the setup screen.
IGameBoard
This is an interface that holds the functions that are necessary in order for a GameBoard to be functional.
TicTacToeController
The TicTacToeController class will handle communication between our TicTacToeView and our model (IGameBoard and BoardPosition)
TicTacToeGame
This class is the entry point of our program and just loads the set up screen and controller.
TicTacToeView
This class is the view of our Extended TicTacToe game our view has a message area, and a list of buttons the buttons will be arranged in a ROWS_IN_BUTTON_PANEL x COLUMNS_IN_BUTTON_PANEL Grid Players will use the buttons to make their next move.
